transcript_llm: Empathy, huh? It's like having that ability to really connect with someone on a deeper level, you know? I totally get what you mean about stepping into someone else's shoes and feeling what they feel. It's like a superpower that lets you see things from a different angle. For me, empathy has been a game-changer in understanding my friends and family better. Like, there was this one time when my friend was going through a tough breakup, and instead of just saying the usual stuff, I really tried to understand what she was going through. And you know what? It made such a difference in how I supported her. Empathy is like a secret weapon for building stronger connections with people, don't you think?
